CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper March 22, 1952, pg. 27, reads: "Junior High Champs - Some of the crack group of Junior High School swimmers that participated in the school boy title meet last week at Allegheny High School pose proudly above. Shown in the top picture are members of Herron Hill's and Westinghouse's crack teams. Lower picture shows, from left to right: William Dapper, Westinghouse, and Victor Hill and Ellis Frank Lily, Herron Hill, winners in that order in the diving competition. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Ten women and girls, posed in audience during junior high school swimming meet at Allegheny High School
